09/01/2004
BERLIN, Germany -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan is in Berlin to attend the International Bertelsmann Forum, which starts Friday (9 January). The focus will be on EU issues. Erdogan's counterparts from Germany, Ireland, Croatia and Romania are also attending, providing an opportunity for bilateral discussions.
In other news, European Commission (EC) President Romano Prodi and EU Enlargement Commissioner Guenter Verheugen will visit Turkey next week, at the invitation of President Ahmet Necdet Sezer. Prodi will be the first EC president to visit Turkey since the 1963 signing of the Ankara Agreement. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 08/01/04)
